Here are some questions about zone transfers I cannot find the
answers to in RFC 1034 or RFC 1035, particulary section 4.3.5 of RFC
1034:

1.  On page 28, RFC 1034 says "The first and last messages [of a zone 
transfer] must contain the data for the top authoritative node of the
zone."  Does just mean all the RR's for the top node (an MX is common)
or just the SOA?  Existing servers seem to just send the SOA.

2.  What RR's should be in each section of the message?  Can there be
more than one RR in a section of the message?  Existing servers seem
to send empty question, authority, and additonal sections and exactly
one RR in the answer section of each message.  BIND seems to abort
an incoming zone transfer if it gets more than one RR in the answer
section.

Bruce Orchard (orchard@waisman.wisc.edu)
University of Wisconsin-Madison

